Apple Spice Dump Cake

4 c chopped fresh apples (~2 large) ex pink lady, fuji, etc)
1 box gf cake mix ex king arthur flour, pamela's or cake therapy
3/4 c butter, melted + more for greasing pan
pinch of cinnamon

Preheat oven to 350F. Grease a 9" square baking dish. Spread the apples in an even layer at the bottom, layer the cake mix on top and drizzle with melted butter. Sprinkle the cinnamon over the top. Bake for 25 min or until top is golden brown. 


**Can substitute other gruits such as cranberries, pears, or plums.

